    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 6790.0,
      "end_time": 9730.0,
      "text": "The result is fantastic vision that allows them"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 9730.0,
      "end_time": 13950.0,
      "text": "to stalk and hunt prey, and make some spectacular jumps."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 13950.0,
      "end_time": 16480.0,
      "text": "But how exactly do those eyes work?"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 16480.0,
      "end_time": 18461.0,
      "text": "Scientists know they interact with each other,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 18461.0,
      "end_time": 19700.0,
      "text": "but in what way?"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 19700.0,
      "end_time": 22420.0,
      "text": "To give a spider an eye test, researchers"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 22420.0,
      "end_time": 25180.0,
      "text": "had to attach the creature to the apparatus."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 25180.0,
      "end_time": 28210.0,
      "text": "They held it down with a plastic and paraffin film"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 28210.0,
      "end_time": 31540.0,
      "text": "and made an opening to dab some wax on the spider head."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 31540.0,
      "end_time": 35090.0,
      "text": "Then, they attached a hat straight out of Dr. Seuss,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 35100.0,
      "end_time": 38100.0,
      "text": "and put the spider in a custom-built eye tracker —"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 38100.0,
      "end_time": 41500.0,
      "text": "one of only two such machines in the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 41500.0,
      "end_time": 43870.0,
      "text": "Held in place on a trackball, the spider"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 43870.0,
      "end_time": 45580.0,
      "text": "watched video images."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 45580.0,
      "end_time": 48160.0,
      "text": "Ultraviolet light penetrated the spider’s head"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 48160.0,
      "end_time": 50419.0,
      "text": "to illuminate what was going on in there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 50420.0,
      "end_time": 52520.0,
      "text": "and researchers aimed a camera at the spider’s"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 52520.0,
      "end_time": 55450.0,
      "text": "two main eyes — the big ones up front."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 55450.0,
      "end_time": 58200.0,
      "text": "Flexible tubes from the eye to the retina"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 58200.0,
      "end_time": 60100.0,
      "text": "allow the spider to look here and there."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 60100.0,
      "end_time": 61672.0,
      "text": "See them moving?"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 61672.0,
      "end_time": 63620.0,
      "text": "Here, the image that the spider is seeing"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 63620.0,
      "end_time": 66140.0,
      "text": "is superimposed over the retinas."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 66140.0,
      "end_time": 67930.0,
      "text": "They look like boomerangs."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 67930.0,
      "end_time": 71370.0,
      "text": "You can see them following the black dot across the screen."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 71370.0,
      "end_time": 74170.0,
      "text": "But the retinas have a small field of vision."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 74170.0,
